The paper is about a machine learning algorithm, specifically the Gradient Boosted Tree (GBT) algorithm, and proposes a new method for dealing with massive datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to scalability and communication efficiency, which could also place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The use of sparsity and the Quickscorer algorithm suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Data Mining (cs.DM) categories. Finally, the mention of Click-Through Rate (CTR) prediction and learning-to-rank suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
